"n. 斗牛士 【英】 n. 斗牛士( a bull fighter) 【例】 The bull tossed the matador into the air. n. (经过最后几轮闪避后将牛杀死的)斗牛士 【记】mat席子, ador = adore(v 崇拜): 令人崇拜的手持席子的人－斗牛士. 【记】match比赛 + adore 崇拜，比赛中崇拜的人，斗牛比赛； mat席子 + adore 喜爱，整天拿着席子并且受人喜爱的人，斗牛士是拿着布也就是席子斗牛的 matador (n.)  man who kills the bull in a bullfight, 1670s, from Spanish matador, literally ""killer,"" from matar ""to kill or wound,"" probably from Arabic mata ""he died,"" from Persian (see second element in checkmate). Fem. form is matadora."
